"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The advertising and marketing industry is probably one of the first industries who will slowly adopt blockchain technology. Especially for the current problems concerning privacy and the pros and cons related to personalized advertising the blockchain offers many useful solutions. First projects like the [brave browser \\\\[LINK\\\\]](https://brave.com/) are already not only being planned, but already finally made ready and now just started to be used.\\n\\nIn my mind everything related to advertising and blockchain has at least a good chance to be successful. However, this is probably a well known competitive market. So the winners from today are maybe the losers from tomorrow and vice versa. I also can imagine that in the future there’s probably also a lot more variety of coins for a lot of special use cases that have to fight for market share and compete for it before being really successful. This can be a very uncertain and hard time for some projects until they can really call them themselves “successful”. Even though I said that the ad and marketing industry is probably one of the first to adopt the blockchain technology I think the process of development (the “surviving of the fittest”) will most likely take a longer time compared to other industries. This is because competition in the advertising industry is often much harder than other sectors like for example data storage.\",\"timestamp\":1639559761,\"title\":\"Huge potential coins: BAT (and the Brave Browser)\"},\"digest\":\"i5rPmM4c9yP8um9iXhbDDkPu_3JWAJeSHeCo_t6Ew9E\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xC6F220eaD0925689cF93F282b18cc3C22B16624b\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"iPR8sGcgpwJ-G1LZln2rhg1JyzFEhaqu2gX_9w4zOgY\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"o_5FyS4bgnz8M-dk_A5puDjwebIbhZdwcBOH507i39k\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"39v_RTC0lGu7SXZmgLogFFQTzFssTRfTRRH9l6x6AR1-ybj7BW9jBbvsutdaVBQtCqiGjdJ3jfqnzY